column3: ﻿RODERICK HUDSON CHAPTER I. Rowland Mallet had made his arrangements to sail for Europe on the first of September, and having in the interval a fortnight to spare, he determined to spend it with his cousin Cecilia,
column4: ﻿RODERICK HUDSON CHAPTER I. Rowland Mallet had made his arrangements to sail for Europe on the first of September, and having in the interval a fortnight to spare, he determined to spend it with his cousin Cecilia,with his hands in his pockets, his legs outstretched, his head thrown back, and his eyes on vacancy, it was to be supposed that his fancy was hovering about the half-shaped image in his studio,

                                                ELIZABETH GASKELL
                                                
                                                
                                                
                                                Oh for thy voice to soothe and bless! What hope of answer, or redress? Behind the veil! Behind the veil! Tennyson CHAPTER I MONKSHAVEN

the reading lamp, and the open books. Margaret and I are sitting together:
                                                her hand is in mine; my heart is with hers. Love, and Youth, andmy heart is with hers. Love, and Youth, and Beauty - the mortal Trinity of this world's worship - are there, in that quiet softly-lit room; but not alone.
